Sprint Plan

Assumption: 2-week sprints, small-to-mid team, capacity around 25-35 points per sprint. Adjust if your team is larger or smaller.

Sprint 1
Goal: remove the most visible demo gaps in agency/recruitment flows and establish basic testing discipline.

Stories:

AGY-101 Real agency client list
AGY-102 Agency client search and filters
REC-301 Real resume upload storage
REC-302 Resume validation and file safeguards
QLT-1101 Replace placeholder unit test script
Estimated capacity:

18-20 points
Milestones:

agency portal no longer shows mock client data
recruitment no longer stores fake resume URLs
test command becomes real and CI-ready
Risks:

storage provider setup for resumes
agency-client ownership mapping may need schema review
Sprint 2
Goal: make commission handling operational instead of approximate.

Stories:

COM-201 Add commission payout data model
COM-202 Agency payout request flow
COM-204 Real payout history table
AGY-103 Agency client detail timeline
Estimated capacity:

18 points
Milestones:

payout workflow exists end-to-end for request side
agency users can see real payout history
client detail becomes actionable for partner operations
Risks:

payout accounting rules may need finance signoff
existing commission assumptions may need backfill logic
Sprint 3
Goal: stabilize finance operations and remove transient reconciliation behavior.

Stories:

FIN-401 Persist reconciliation sessions
FIN-402 Persist match/ignore decisions
FIN-404 Normalize reconciliation status model
Estimated capacity:

16 points
Milestones:

reconciliation becomes auditable
users can revisit prior sessions
UI/backend status model is consistent
Risks:

data model design for imported statements
migration complexity if current users already rely on existing behavior
Sprint 4
Goal: improve finance dashboard trustworthiness.

Stories:

FIN-501 Real finance trend deltas
FIN-502 Dynamic cashflow forecast widget
FIN-503 Analytics period controls
COM-203 Finance payout review workflow
Estimated capacity:

16 points
Milestones:

finance dashboard no longer shows demo-style trend logic
payout lifecycle includes finance-side approval and payment completion
Risks:

forecasting logic may require product agreement on formula
payout approvals may need role/permission refinement
